#: prompts/actions.lua:192
msgid ""
"Simplifies the passage into everyday language using analogies and concrete "
"examples, without sacrificing accuracy."
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:209
msgid "Summarize"
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:210
msgid ""
"Condenses the selected passage to its essential points, keeping what matters "
"and trimming the rest."
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:225
msgid "Elaborate"
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:226
msgid ""
"Expands on the passage by unpacking concepts, adding context, and exploring "
"implications."
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:240
msgid "Connect"
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:241
msgid ""
"Finds connections between the passage and broader themes, other works, "
"thinkers, and intellectual traditions."
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:264
msgid "Connect (With Notes)"
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:265
msgid ""
"Connects the passage to your own highlights and notebook entries, revealing "
"patterns and echoes in your reading. Requires annotations and notebook "
"sharing to be enabled."
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:305
msgid "Explain in Context"
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:306
msgid ""
"Helps you understand what a passage means — its content, context, and the "
"ideas it builds on. Comprehension-focused. Works well for longer or "
"particularly difficult passages that benefit from document context."
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:337
msgid "Analyze in Context"
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:338
msgid ""
"Connects the passage to your own reading — your highlights, annotations, "
"notebook entries, and the threads you've been tracking. Reader-focused, not "
"just content-focused."
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:381
msgid "Thematic Connection"
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:382
msgid ""
"Examines the author's craft — how language, structure, and technique achieve "
"the passage's effect, and how it fits into the work's thematic architecture."
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:420
msgid "Fact Check"
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:421
msgid ""
"Searches the web to verify claims in the selected passage, rating accuracy "
"and citing current sources as evidence."
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:450
msgid "Current Context"
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:451
msgid ""
"Searches the web for the latest developments on the topic discussed in the "
"selected passage — what has changed since it was written."
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:480
msgid ""
"Generates a Wikipedia-style encyclopedia entry about the selected text, "
"using AI knowledge and optionally web search for current information."
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:514
msgid "Grammar"
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:515
msgid ""
"Breaks down sentence structure with constituency parse and word-by-word "
"grammatical analysis. Shows both modern linguistic and traditional "
"frameworks for Classical Arabic."
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:549
msgid "Look up in X-Ray"
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:550
msgid ""
"Search X-Ray cache for selected text. Local lookup — no AI call, works "
"offline."
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:929
msgid ""
"Comprehensive overview: what the work is about, its themes, significance, "
"and reading experience. Based on AI knowledge — no book data needed."
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:975
msgid "Find Similar"
