msgid "About Author"
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:1006
msgid ""
"Biography, major works, writing style, and suggested reading order for the "
"author."
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:1018
msgid "Historical Context"
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:1019
msgid ""
"Explores when the work was written, what was happening at the time, and how "
"it reflects or responds to its era."
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:1034
msgid ""
"Builds a structured reference guide — characters, themes, locations, "
"timeline — up to your current reading position. Completely spoiler-free. "
"When highlights are shared, adds a reader engagement section analyzing what "
"catches your attention. Updates incrementally as you read further. Can also "
"target a specific section from the table of contents."
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:1037
msgid "Or use X-Ray (Simple) for an overview based on AI knowledge."
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:1130
msgid ""
"A prose companion guide from AI knowledge — characters, themes, settings, "
"key terms. No text extraction needed. Uses reading progress to avoid "
"spoilers. Highlights add personal context when shared."
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:1221
msgid ""
"A 'Previously on...' refresher to help you get back into reading after time "
"away. Covers recent events, active threads, and where you left off. Adapts "
"to fiction or non-fiction. When highlights are shared, weaves in what you "
"found notable. Updates incrementally as you read further."
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:1307 prompts/actions.lua:1815
msgid "Analyze Notes"
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:1308
msgid ""
"Analyzes your note-taking and highlighting patterns to reveal what catches "
"your attention, emerging themes, and connections between your notes. This is "
"about understanding you as a reader, not summarizing the work."
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:1370
msgid "Related Thinkers"
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:1371
msgid ""
"Maps the intellectual landscape: who influenced the author, who the author "
"influenced, and contemporary thinkers working on similar problems. For "
"fiction, focuses on literary influences and movements."
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:1407
msgid ""
"Breaks down the work's thesis, supporting arguments, evidence, assumptions, "
"and potential counterarguments. For fiction, analyzes themes and the "
"author's worldview instead. Can target a specific section. Result is saved "
"as an artifact."
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:1460
msgid ""
"Generates 8-10 discussion questions spanning comprehension, analysis, "
"interpretation, and personal connection. Good for book clubs or classroom "
"use. Can target a specific section. Result is saved as an artifact."
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:1508
msgid ""
"Interactive comprehension quiz with multiple choice, short answer, and essay "
"questions. Answers one at a time with scoring. Result is saved as an "
"artifact. Can be triggered automatically at chapter ends."
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:1536
msgid "Document Analysis"
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:1537
msgid ""
"Analyzes the document's thesis, structure, key insights, and audience. The "
"result is saved as an Analyze artifact that other actions can reference. Can "
"target a specific section."
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:1570
msgid "Document Summary"
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:1571
msgid ""
"Creates a comprehensive summary preserving key details and structure. The "
"result is saved as a Summary artifact, which other actions can use as their "
"document source. Can target a specific section."
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:1596
msgid "Extract Key Insights"
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:1597
msgid ""
"Distills the most important takeaways: ideas worth remembering, novel "
"perspectives, actionable conclusions, and connections to broader concepts. "
"Can target a specific section. Result is saved as an artifact."
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:1633
msgid ""
"A spoiler-free guide to what's ahead — themes developing, questions worth "
"holding, patterns to notice. Uses your reading position to stay safe. Can "
"target a specific section."
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:1681
msgid "Suggest from Library"
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:1682
msgid ""
"Suggests what to read next from your own library, based on the current book "
"and your reading history."
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:1686 prompts/actions.lua:1841 prompts/actions.lua:1859
#: prompts/actions.lua:1876
msgid ""
"Enable library scanning in Settings → Privacy & Data to use this action."
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:1704
msgid "Reviews"
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:1705
msgid ""
"Searches the web for critical and reader reviews, awards, and any "
"controversy about the work."
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:1735
msgid "Compare"
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:1736
msgid ""
"Compares the selected works, focusing on meaningful contrasts: different "
"approaches, unique strengths, and which readers would prefer which."
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:1748
msgid "Find Common Themes"
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:1749
msgid ""
"Identifies shared themes, intellectual traditions, and deeper patterns "
"across the selected works — beyond surface-level genre labels."
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:1761
msgid "Analyze Collection"
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:1762
msgid ""
"Analyzes what the collection reveals about the reader's interests, "
"perspective, and what might be missing for a more complete picture."
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:1775
msgid "Quick Summaries"
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:1776
msgid ""
"A brief 2-3 sentence summary of each selected work, focusing on premise and "
"appeal."
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:1788
msgid "Reading Order"
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:1789
msgid ""
"Suggests an optimal reading order based on conceptual dependencies, "
"difficulty progression, and thematic arc."
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:1801
msgid "Recommend"
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:1802
msgid ""
"Recommends 5-8 new works based on the patterns across your selected works — "
"matching the intersection of your interests, not just similarity to one "
"title. When library scanning is enabled, notes which recommendations you "
"already own and prioritizes books you haven't read."
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:1816
msgid ""
"Analyzes your highlights, annotations, and notes across the selected books — "
"what patterns emerge in what you mark, what you write, and how your thinking "
"connects across works."
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:1820
msgid ""
"Enable highlights or annotations sharing in Settings → Privacy & Data to use "
"this action."
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:1834
msgid "Next Read"
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:1835
msgid ""
"Suggests what to read next from your library — including books worth "
"revisiting or picking back up. Based on what you've finished recently, "
"what's been sitting unread, and your reading patterns. When advanced stats "
"are enabled, includes engagement context like books you've stalled on or "
"read extensively."
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:1852
msgid "Discover New"
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:1853
msgid ""
"Suggests new books based on your library — identifies your taste from what "
"you own and recommends works you don't have yet, including a few picks "
"outside your comfort zone. When advanced stats are enabled, uses engagement "
"data to better understand your preferences."
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:1869
msgid "Analyze Library"
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:1870
msgid ""
"Analyzes your library to reveal genres and authors you gravitate toward, "
"completion patterns, and gaps in your collection. When advanced stats are "
"enabled, includes engagement insights like which books you spent the most "
"time on."
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:1891
msgid "News Update"
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:1892
msgid ""
"Fetches today's top global news stories from Al Jazeera with headlines, "
"summaries, and links. Uses web search."
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:1920
msgid ""
"Translates the selected text into your configured translation language. This "
"action also controls the Translate Current Page function."
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:1939
msgid "Quick Define"
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:1940
msgid ""
"A brief, one-line dictionary definition of the selected word in your "
"dictionary language."
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:1970
msgid ""
"Full dictionary entry with pronunciation, definitions, etymology, and "
"synonyms."
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:2001
msgid "Deep Analysis"
msgstr ""

#: prompts/actions.lua:2002
msgid ""
"Deep linguistic analysis covering morphology, word family, etymology, "
"cognates, and cross-language borrowings. Adapts to the word's language "
"family (Semitic roots, Indo-European stems, etc.)."
msgstr ""
